Cell.Text: Always was a stubborn woman. She's not going to stand down.
War always comes down to this, doesn't it? A single truth-laden moment.
Dragonborn... Perhaps this is the fate of Skryim after all. To be destroyed from the inside.
Just kill her and get it over with.
G|You're a cold hearted bastard, aren't you?
Just kill her and get it over with.
G|I fear that will be the way of it.
We'll kill you if we must.
G|A true Nord never fears death. It's the how and why of it that one needs consider.
You're not going to kill her, are you?
G|Aye, I'll hate it, but I'll do it if I have to.
You're not going to kill her, are you?
G|That's up to her, isn't it?
Rikke, leave. They'll kill you.
G|If that must be, then it will. And why should I be any different? How many the lives already lost. What's one more?
Well, Dragonborn. What do you say? Do you want the honor?
Song or not, I just want it done. | Will you do this?
[S] G|As you wish.
[S] G|Well, I'm not quite done myself.

Node.Caption: CWFinaleExecutionTopicChoice1: I've had my fair share of killing today.

Cell.Text: [S] G|As you wish. This moment, we three, will be immortalized in song.
I won't give him the satisfaction.
[S] G|Fine by me.
[S] G|Dragonborn. Here, use my sword to do it. This moment will be immortalized in song. Make it a good kill.
[S] G|Here, use my sword to do it. I made sure to sharpen it for the occasion.
[S] G|Oh, and Legate. It's been an honor to have you at my side. As token of my appreciation, I want you to keep my sword. | And now, to deliver a speech. Let's go.

Stormblade. I want you to have my sword, a token of my appreciation. | Now then. The men will expect a speech. Will you stand by my side? I wish to honor you, Dragonborn and the truest of Stormcloaks.
The men will expect a speech. Will you stand by my side? I wish to honor you, Dragonborn and the truest of Stormcloaks.
[S] G|Very good. Come, the people await us.
Oh, why is that?

Node.Caption: CWFinaleLeaveMeOut: Maybe you should leave me out of your speech.

Cell.Text: On the contrary, you exceed the rest. | But, I will honor your request. The gods know of your victories, and they themselves will glory in your deeds.

Node.Caption: CWFinaleManyDied: Many have fought and died. I am no different than they.

Cell.Text: There's no shame in such thoughts. A man without doubts is a man without a conscience. | But rest assured. We've won Skyrim's right to determine her own future. And for that, every Nord praises us. | But I will heed your wishes.

Node.Caption: CWFinaleNotWorthIt: I'm not sure this was all worth it, after all.

Cell.Text: A man's heart is his own burden to bear, so I will honor your request, though it casts a bit of gloom on an otherwise glorious day.
[S] G|Come, at the very least walk out with me.
GS|I'm ready. I made my peace with the gods long ago.
G|What are you waiting for? Do it!
GS|With me, you kill Skyrim's last hope. Mark my words. You'll all be serving elvish masters soon enough. Know then, that I would have stopped them.
G|By the gods, stop toying with me and do it!
